reviews.name: Glory Mathew
reviews.text:
Came here with my husband to check jaundice for our baby. The whole KK was packed with people when we came. There was no proper process flow. We took the ticket and registered then we wasted a lot of time waiting to be called, not knowing that we needed to go to the counter to inform them again then we had to proceed to timbang our baby. Thank God for sending a kind soul to us to guide us what to do. I saw many people came in looking so lost not knowing where to go or what to do.

The number system also was very bad, after giving the blood test to the lab we waited there to be called as this was the process flow last year when we were here. Not knowing that they were calling our number at another side for consultation. The number system on left and right side are different which makes it really confusing.

My nurse from KK Metro Prima informed KK Kelana Jaya that I will be doing confinement under KK Kelana Jaya expecting someone would call to come for house visit but nobody called about that, only called to ask about bringing baby for jaundice test. Last year when I was doing confinement when I had my first child also the same thing, my nurse from KK Metro Prima informed KK Kota Damansara as she thought Bandar Utama is under that area to come for house visiting but they too didn‚Äôt visit.

Im very disappointed with many of the KK service even though it‚Äôs free, except for KK Metro Prima, a small KK in a shop lot which is more family friendly where most of the nurses are polite, friendly and helpful.

reviews.name: Rayan8888
reviews.text: Came to the klinik on 13/10 as per scheduled appointment. The call number system was down and the place turned into a madhouse. The staff behind counters C to F tried calling numbers manually. Their voices did not carry. Challenging for persons like me who is difficult of hearing. Fortunately one Mr Indera Shah came out of the cubicle and organized the number/name calling. This action helped clear the queue. Kudos to him for the initiative. He's also very patient and understanding.

reviews.name: Soon Jeffrey
reviews.text:
I never had good experiences here. Bad number calling system. No proper process flow. I wasted a lot of time waited for nothing only to find out I have to put baby book into tray.

On one occasion I had to feed baby while my wife went for checkup. It was my first time visit KK. I proceeded to use the nursery/changing room unknowingly male cannot enter. Mid feeding I was told off by a nurse rudely I wasn't allowed to use the nursery room. I felt so much disrespect and discrimination. I had to carry a bagpack and baby out to continue feeding while standing. Are they discriminating single male parents out there??

Though the KK treatment is cheap and/or free,we as patron deserve basic respect and decency as human being receiving medical care. This is not a prison or juvenile centre. We don't owe them anything. They are taking gov salary and benefits.

Separate occasion my wife use the same nursery room to make baby milk,she noticed some cockroach feces on the table.

There's one time I overheard a nurse talking very rudely to an elderly. The nurse was scolding the Chinese old grandmother why you never come to this station earlier/faster when I call your number so many times. I was so dumbfounded to hear she said that out loud. I cannot tolerate this kind of manner.

We as citizen enjoying our rights and benefits receiving cheap/free healthcare but downside we gotta see/face the nurses' sour face,rude and unfriendly manner.

P.S: nurses didn't listen to my wife's question properly and simply give an answer. üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

Don't give me that "it's cheap and free,if you don't like/not happy then don't go" bullshit. Being a cheap/free healthcare doesn't give them the entitlement to treat citizen/patron poorly. Especially elderly!
